OL,3,CThe thorn in Labour's side: Will
OL,4,CStarmer scrap the two-child benefit
OL,5,Ccap?
OL,7,FBut the cap has since attracted fierce
OL,8,Fcriticism from children's charities,
OL,9,Freligious figures and increasingly
OL,10,FLabour politicians, who say it has
OL,11,Fexacerbated the number of children in
OL,12,Fpoverty in the UK - which now stands
OL,13,Fat 4.3 million.
OL,15,FDuring the Labour leadership race in
OL,16,F2020, Sir Keir Starmer advocated
OL,17,Fscrapping the policy as part of plans
OL,18,Fto "tackle the vast social injustice
OL,19,Fin our country".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
