OL,5,Ccap?
OL,7,FHe later reversed his position in
OL,8,F2023, much to the frustration of those
OL,9,Fon the left of his party - citing the
OL,10,Ftough economic conditions that a
OL,11,FLabour government could be set to
OL,12,Finherit and an unwillingness to make
OL,13,Funfunded spending commitments.
OL,15,FBut with Labour now in power, many
OL,16,Fwithin the party have begun to
OL,17,Fprivately - and publicly -voice alarm
OL,18,Fat the continuation of the policy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
