OL,3,CThe thorn in Labour's side: Will
OL,4,CStarmer scrap the two-child benefit
OL,5,Ccap?
OL,7,FThe Resolution Foundation has
OL,8,Festimated that scrapping the policy
OL,9,Fwould lift around 490,000 children out
OL,10,Fof poverty, at the cost of between
OL,11,F#2.5 billion and #3.6 billion.
OL,13,FIn their manifesto, Labour promised an
OL,14,F"ambitious strategy to reduce child
OL,15,Fpoverty", including introducing free
OL,16,Fbreakfast clubs within primary schools.
OL,18,FAnd in a statement, Work and Pensions
OL,19,FSecretary Liz Kendall said: "Too many
OL,20,Fchildren are growing up in poverty and
OL,21,Fthis is a stain on our society."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
